                     <interp inst="t18320105-204-defend1803" type="age" value="22"></interp>
                  </persName>
               
             was indicted for <rs id="t18320105-204-off1134" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18320105-204-off1134" type="offenceCategory" value="theft"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18320105-204-off1134" type="offenceSubcategory" value="simpleLarceny"></interp>
               stealing, on the <rs id="t18320105-204-cd1135" type="crimeDate">3rd of January</rs>
                     <join result="offenceCrimeDate" targOrder="Y" targets="t18320105-204-off1134 t18320105-204-cd1135"></join>, 4 handkerchiefs, value 16s.; 1 pair of stockings, value 6s., and 12 yards of ribbon, value 16s.
            </rs>, the goods of 
               
                  <persName id="t18320105-204-victim1805" type="victimName">
                     Samuel 
                     Strong
                  <interp inst="t18320105-204-victim1805" type="surname" value="Strong"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18320105-204-victim1805" type="given" value="Samuel"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18320105-204-victim1805" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
               
             and 
               
                  <persName id="t18320105-204-victim1807" type="victimName">
                     Richard 
                     Woolley
                  <interp inst="t18320105-204-victim1807" type="surname" value="Woolley"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18320105-204-victim1807" type="given" value="Richard"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18320105-204-victim1807" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
               
            .</p>
               <p>CHARLES SCOTT. I am in the service of Messrs. Strong and Woolley - they are <rs id="t18320105-204-viclabel1136" type="occupation">silk-mercer</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18320105-204-victim1805 t18320105-204-viclabel1136"></join>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18320105-204-victim1807 t18320105-204-viclabel1136"></join>s. On the 3rd of January, about noon, the prisoner came to their shop - she purchased a number of articles, which came to 4l. 13s.; she desired them to be sent to a direction which she gave; I mentioned it to Mr. Woolley, who followed her.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18320105-204-person1808">
                  RICHARD 
                  WOOLLEY
               <interp inst="t18320105-204-person1808" type="surname" value="WOOLLEY"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18320105-204-person1808" type="given" value="RICHARD"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18320105-204-person1808" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am in partnership with Mr. Samuel Strong. On the 3rd of January I followed the prisoner to her lodgings, in Peter-street, Cow-cross - I first saw her on the stairs; I got her to come down, and sent the boy for an officer - she denied any knowledge of me, but I told her she had been in my shop a short time before, and if she would give up what property she had of mine, I would suspend the charge, if the constable would; she then took me up stairs to her room, and gave me two silk handkerchiefs out of her bed, which was turned up; I said she must have some ribbon - she then produced this ribbon; the officer then came, and he found these other handkerchiefs and stockings in the bed.(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18320105-204-person1809">
                  RICHARD 
                  MILLEN
               <interp inst="t18320105-204-person1809" type="surname" value="MILLEN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18320105-204-person1809" type="given" value="RICHARD"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18320105-204-person1809" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am an officer. I found these handkerchiefs and stockings doubled up in the bed; this ribbon and these other handkerchiefs the prosecutor had in his hand.</p>
               <p>JURY. Q. Did any one else occupy that room? A. The person who let the room said it was let to the prisoner only.</p>
               <p>The prisoner put in a written Defence, pleading poverty, and expressing her contrition.</p>
               <p>GUILTY. Aged 22.</p>
               <p>
